    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Try <a href=\"http://static.javadoc.io/org.cactoos/cactoos/0.20.2/org/cactoos/list/StickyList.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>StickyList</code></a> from <a href=\"http://www.cactoos.org\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Cactoos</a>:</p>\n\n<pre><code>List&lt;String&gt; list = new StickyList&lt;&gt;(iterable);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Disclaimer: I'm one of the developers.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1521739,
      "reputation" : 4112,
      "user_id" : 1421194,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 73,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/243fd9ab65afa72526f32181cfcd5886?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Sasha",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1421194/sasha"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 2,
    "last_activity_date" : 1508466270,
    "creation_date" : 1508466270,
    "answer_id" : 46841518,
    "question_id" : 10117026,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I just want to point out a seemingly obvious solution that <strong>will NOT</strong> work:</p>\n\n<pre>\n<s>List list = Stream.generate(iterator::next)\n    .collect(Collectors.toList());</s>\n</pre>\n\n<p>That's because <a href=\"//docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/stream/Stream.html#generate-java.util.function.Supplier-\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>Stream#generate(Supplier&lt;T&gt;)</code></a> can create only infinite streams, it doesn't expect its argument to throw <a href=\"//docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/NoSuchElementException.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>NoSuchElementException</code></a> (that's what <a href=\"//docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/Iterator.html#next--\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>Iterator#next()</code></a> will do in the end).</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"//stackoverflow.com/a/23997880\">The xehpuk's answer</a> should be used instead if the Iterator→Stream→List way is your choice.</p>\n"
  }, {
